quran[33]{c,v,t}:
  55,46,For those who fear of standing before their Lord will be two Gardens
  55,47,"Then which of the favors of your Lord will you [men and jinn] deny"
  55,48,Shaded by spreading branches
  55,49,"Then which of the favors of your Lord will you [men and jinn] deny"
  55,50,In each there are two flowing springs
  55,51,"Then which of the favors of your Lord will you [men and jinn] deny"
  55,52,In each there are two kinds of every fruit
  55,53,"Then which of the favors of your Lord will you [men and jinn] deny"
  55,54,"They will recline on couches lined with rich brocade, with the fruits of both gardens within reach"
  55,55,"Then which of the favors of your Lord will you [men and jinn] deny"
  55,56,"In them there will be maidens of restrained gaze, untouched before them by any man or jinn"
  55,57,"Then which of the favors of your Lord will you [men and jinn] deny"
  55,58,As if they were rubies and pearls
  55,59,"Then which of the favors of your Lord will you [men and jinn] deny"
  55,60,Is the reward for goodness anything but goodness
  55,61,"Then which of the favors of your Lord will you [men and jinn] deny"
  55,62,And besides these two there will be two other gardens
  55,63,"Then which of the favors of your Lord will you [men and jinn] deny"
  55,64,Both of deepest green
  55,65,"Then which of the favors of your Lord will you [men and jinn] deny"
  55,66,In each there are two gushing springs
  55,67,"Then which of the favors of your Lord will you [men and jinn] deny"
  55,68,"In each there are fruits, palm trees, and pomegranates"
  55,69,"Then which of the favors of your Lord will you [men and jinn] deny"
  55,70,In them there are beautiful noble women
  55,71,"Then which of the favors of your Lord will you [men and jinn] deny"
  55,72,"Maidens with gorgeous eyes, secluded in pavilions"
  55,73,"Then which of the favors of your Lord will you [men and jinn] deny"
  55,74,No human or jinn has ever touched them before
  55,75,"Then which of the favors of your Lord will you [men and jinn] deny"
  55,76,"[They will be] reclining on green cushions and splendid carpets"
  55,77,"Then which of the favors of your Lord will you [men and jinn] deny"
  55,78,"Blessed is the Name of your Lord, the Lord of Majesty and Honor"